</div>
			<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading" lang="en">H. K. Edgerton</h1>
									<div id="bodyContent" class="mw-body-content">
									<div id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>
								<div id="contentSub"></div>
												<div id="jump-to-nav" class="mw-jump">
					Jump to:					<a href="#mw-head">navigation</a>, 					<a href="#p-search">search</a>
				</div>
				<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><table class="metadata plainlinks ambox ambox-content ambox-BLP_sources" role="presentation">
<tr>
<td class="mbox-image">
<div style="width:52px"><img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b4/Ambox_important.svg/40px-Ambox_important.svg.png" width="40" height="40" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b4/Ambox_important.svg/60px-Ambox_important.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b4/Ambox_important.svg/80px-Ambox_important.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="40" data-file-height="40" /></div>
</td>
<td class="mbox-text"><span class="mbox-text-span">This <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Biographies_of_living_persons" title="Wikipedia:Biographies of living persons">biographical article</a> <b>needs additional <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Citing_sources" title="Wikipedia:Citing sources">citations</a> for <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Verifiability" title="Wikipedia:Verifiability">verification</a></b>. <span class="hide-when-compact">Please help by adding <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Identifying_reliable_sources" title="Wikipedia:Identifying reliable sources">reliable sources</a>. Contentious material about living persons that is unsourced or poorly sourced <b>must be removed immediately</b>, especially if potentially <a href="/wiki/Defamation" title="Defamation">libelous</a> or harmful.</span> <small><i>(April 2014)</i></small></span></td>
</tr>
</table>
<p><b>H. K. Edgerton</b> is an <a href="/wiki/African-American" title="African-American" class="mw-redirect">African-American</a> <a href="/wiki/Activist" title="Activist" class="mw-redirect">activist</a> for <a href="/wiki/U.S._Southern_states" title="U.S. Southern states" class="mw-redirect">Southern</a> heritage and an African-American member of the <a href="/wiki/Sons_of_Confederate_Veterans" title="Sons of Confederate Veterans">Sons of Confederate Veterans</a>. He often is given a prominent place at rallies for the <a href="/wiki/Confederate_flag" title="Confederate flag" class="mw-redirect">Confederate flag</a>. A former <a href="/wiki/President" title="President">president</a> of the <a href="/wiki/Asheville,_North_Carolina" title="Asheville, North Carolina">Asheville, North Carolina</a> chapter of the <a href="/wiki/NAACP" title="NAACP" class="mw-redirect">NAACP</a> (National Association for the Advancement of Colored People), he is on the board of the <a href="/wiki/Southern_Legal_Resource_Center" title="Southern Legal Resource Center">Southern Legal Resource Center</a>.</p>
<p></p>
